properties.headline: Winter Storm Watch issued January 15 at 10:28PM CST until January 18 at 6:00PM CST by NWS Twin Cities/Chanhassen MN
properties.description:
...Wind Chill Advisory tonight....

...Winter Storm Watch Friday through Saturday...

.Wind chill values will be between -20 to -35 tonight. Wind chill
values will slowly improve Thursday morning.

Accumulating snow will develop across Minnesota Friday morning and
move into western Wisconsin early Friday afternoon. Snow will
begin to taper off late Friday night into Saturday morning, but
northwest winds will be increasing then, with blowing and
drifting snow becoming an increasing hazard on Saturday,
especially in open areas of western into southern Minnesota.
Currently, 7 to 10 inches of snow is expected across much of
central and southern Minnesota and western Wisconsin

* WHAT...For the Wind Chill Advisory, very cold wind chills
expected. Wind chills as low as 30 below zero. For the Winter
Storm Watch, heavy snow possible. Total snow accumulations of
6 to 9 inches possible. Winds could gust as high as 45 mph.

* WHERE...Todd, Stearns and Meeker Counties.

* WHEN...For the Wind Chill Advisory, from 9 PM this evening to
9 AM CST Thursday. For the Winter Storm Watch, from Friday
morning through Saturday afternoon.

* IMPACTS...Travel could be very difficult. Areas of blowing snow
could significantly reduce visibility. The hazardous conditions
could impact evening commute Friday. The dangerously cold wind
chills could cause frostbite on exposed skin in as little as 10
minutes.
properties.instruction:
Use caution while traveling outside. Wear appropriate clothing, a
hat, and gloves.

Monitor the latest forecasts for updates on this situation.
